[SN]TITLE[SN]
Helium balloons in Loch Creran spark lifeboat and helicopter search

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Helium balloons floating in a sea loch have sparked a lifeboat and coastguard rescue helicopter search operation.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Oban RNLI were called into action following reports that a paraglider was in difficulty in Loch Creran, in Argyll, shortly after 19:00 on Tuesday.
A local fish farm vessel also offered its assistance.
However, the volunteer crew called off the search after realising it was a false alarm.
